## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent data and the inherent complexity of economic systems, which makes it difficult to predict the precise outcomes of targeting zero inflation. Additionally, the perspectives included are primarily from Western economic institutions, which may not fully represent global economic conditions or the views of all economists.